    <id>http://www.prelude-siem.org/issues/327?journal_id=1291</id>
    <updated>2009-06-04T09:46:52Z</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Yoann VANDOORSELAERE</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Status&lt;/strong&gt; changed from &lt;i&gt;New&lt;/i&gt; to &lt;i&gt;Rejected&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;When trying to delete a lot of alerts/heartbeats at once, there might be a failure if the resulting SQL query is bigger than the &lt;em&gt;max_allowed_packet&lt;/em&gt; MySQL settings. &lt;br /&gt;In order to fix this problem, you could either:
	&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Split up the deletion in part &lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Modify your MySQL configuration to increase the value for &lt;em&gt;max_allowed_packet&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;    </content>
